          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Active target detector Array for Nuclear Astrophysics",
                "and Structure with Exotic Nuclei (ANASEN) was filled",
                "with 4He as the target gas including a 4% admixture",
                "of CO2 as a quenching gas, at a pressure of 379 Torr.",
                "The beam particles entered the gas volume through an",
                "8.9 mu-m Kapton window, in which they lost 9 MeV of",
                "energy, and proceeded through the target gas to a",
                "range of 59 cm after the window"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The ANASEN detector systems were arranged in",
                "concentric layers surrounding the beam axis,",
                "starting from an inner set of 24 position-sensitive",
                "proportional-counter anodes at radius of 3.75 cm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detector ended with a layer of 24 position-",
                "sensitive silicon-strip detectors of the Micron",
                "Semiconductor Super-X3 design at a radius of 8.9 cm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four silicon-strip detectors of the Micron",
                "Semiconductor QQQ3 design covered forward laboratory",
                "angles in an annular geometry"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A high-rate, compact ion chamber, sensitive to",
                "heavy ions traveling within 2.2 cm of the beam axis,",
                "including both beam particles and reaction residues.",
                "The ion chamber drift field was created between a",
                "negatively biased (-200 V) tungsten-wire cathode on",
                "the beam axis and 48 anode wires surrounding it at",
                "radius of 2.2 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 18Ne beam was produced via the 16-O(3He,n)18Ne",
                "reaction and selected at 80 MeV and at an average beam",
                "intensity of 2E+3 pps."
              ]
            }
          ],
